ler second line under the main center text."},"968":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-11","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#legend-placement","content":"Switch `legend` to `right` to sit the legend beside the donut, or `bottom` to stack it underneath. `legendLabel` is there when you want a title above the legend items."},"969":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#small-slices","content":"Very thin slices can be noisy to hover. Anything at or below `smallSliceThreshold` (default `0.05` of the total) is treated as “small,” and if those slices sit next to each other on the ring, one hover opens a single tooltip that lists the whole group."},"970":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#format-value","content":"Use `formatValue` when the raw numbers in the tooltip should read like money, counts with separators, or whatever your product expects. The percentage of the total still formats on its own; your function only shapes the value column."},"971":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","type":"page","content":"LineChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart"},"972":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","content":"Line Chart shows how something changes over time or along a continuous scale. It connects data points with lines so people can quickly spot trends, peaks, dips, and patterns."},"973":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/compon